name: aerial-photography-and-imagery-ortho-corrected-2007-digital-orthophotos-fdem-lee-county
notes: This data set is one component of the Florida Division of Emergency Management's (FDEM) Project Management and Technical Services for Mapping within Coastal Florida (Contract 07-HS-34-14-00-22-469), encompassing the entire coastline of Florida. The dataset is comprised of orthophoto imagery, which is a digital image (raster) map produced from aerial imagery that has been rectified to correct for aircraft tilt, terrain relief, and camera/sensor lens distortion. The resulting image has a consistent scale throughout, allowing the user to take direct measurements such as distances, angles, positions, and areas. In accordance with the Baseline Specifications 1.2, the imagery is delivered in GeoTIFF and MrSID formats based on the FDEM's 5,000' by 5,000' grid. Image resolution is 0.5-foot pixels. The digital elevation model (DEM) used for orthorectification was developed from new LiDAR data acquired by the Woolpert Team for the FDEM project. Both natural color and color infrared imagery were produced. The horizontal accuracy requirement is a verified 3.8 feet at the 95% confidence interval (2.2 feet RMSE) as specified in the FGDC Geospatial Positioning Accuracy Standards, Part 3: National Standard for Spatial Data Accuracy (http://www.fgdc.gov/standards/projects/FGDC-standards-projects/accuracy/part3/index_html).
